{{nihongo|'''''Dead or Alive: Paradise'''''|<U+30C7><U+30C3><U+30C9><U+30AA><U+30A2><U+30A2><U+30E9><U+30A4><U+30D6><U+30D1><U+30E9><U+30C0><U+30A4><U+30B9>|Deddo oa Araibu Paradaisu}} is a [[2010 in video gaming|2010]] [[video game]] developed by [[Team Ninja]] and published by [[Tecmo Koei]] for the [[PlayStation Portable]] as part of the ''[[Dead or Alive (series)|Dead or Alive]]'' series. The game is a port and a remake of ''[[Dead or Alive Xtreme 2]]'' for the [[Xbox 360]],<ref name="Release">{{cite web |url=http://psp.ign.com/articles/106/1065902p1.html|title=Tecmo Koei Delays Major Titles in Japan|author=Anoop Gantayat|publisher=[[IGN]]|accessdate=February 16, 2010}}</ref> and the title expands upon the activities available in the original which consisted of mainly beach-related [[mini-game]]s. The game was released in all regions during March and April, 2010.<ref name="Release"/> This is the third title in the ''Dead or Alive'' series for the PlayStation system.

==Plot==
Players start the game at the getaway resort, New [[List of characters in the Dead or Alive series#Zack|Zack Island]], as part of a two week vacation. The island is inhabited mostly by the [[swimsuit]]-clad girls from the ''Dead or Alive'' series.<ref name="Press Release">{{cite web|url=http://psp.ign.com/articles/106/1063199p1.html|title=Dead or Alive Paradise Gives You Paradise in the Palm of Your Hand|author=[[Tecmo Koei]]|date=January 25, 2010|publisher=[[IGN]]|accessdate=February 16, 2010}}</ref>

